SIMPLE: schoolmaster
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Schoolmaster
<hw>School"mas`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
man who presides over and teaches a school; a male teacher of a
school.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let the soldier be abroad if he will; he can do nothing in this
age. There is another personage abroad, -- a person less imposing, -- in
the eyes of some, perhaps, insignificant. The <qex>schoolmaster</qex> is
abroad; and I trust to him, armed with his primer, against the soldier
in full military array.</q> <rj><qau>Brougham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, disciplines and
directs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The law was our <qex>schoolmaster</qex>, to bring us unto
Christ.</q> <rj><qau>Gal. iii. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1287 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><ent>Schoolmate</ent>⟦br⟧
